research_municipality_step.notes: White Oak city, TX operates under a Home Rule charter with attributes of both mayor-council and council-manager forms of government. The mayor operates under a weak-mayor system, and a City Coordinator (City Manager) handles administrative duties. Council members are elected by 'Place' rather than geographical wards or districts. The terms for Council Members Place 1, 2, and 3 expire in May 2025, while the Mayor and Council Members Place 4 and 5 expire in May 2026.
